<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-94-0592 </DOCNO><TEXT>Two years ago, a status report directed particularly at politicians waswritten on the problems of room air quality in indoor areas. The articleis a precise summary of developments in the intervening period and thesuccess achieved by the demand, resulting from public interest, for aquantification of the health hazard posed by indoor air pollution. Thereare comments on the guide figures, municipal limits, limit concentration(dose as a pollution assessment in air hygiene terms, protection valueof limits), the definition of the target group and the dirt content ofthe room air. Details given concern the sources of indoor air pollution,the handling of chemicals in enclosed rooms where people are present,the reduction of air impurities in private rooms, legal measures, airpollution as a result of conversion work, mineral fibres, formaldehyde,wood preservatives, combustion pollution, and radonbenzole, sulphur dioxide,nitrogen oxide, carbon monoxide, ozone, ground emissions and buried waste.(HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>